


 *****************  /usr/ipsc/examples/README  ********************


    This directory contains example programs for the iPSC.  Two directories,
    nx_c and nx_rmf, are C and FORTRAN language versions of example programs.  
    The other directory, rmfort_vx, contains subdirectories that include 
    examples for using the VX machine (if you have installed vector software),
    using veclib routines in a standard cube, and using veclib routines with
    the simulator on a 310.  Each of the sub-directories has its own README
    file with more information on using the examples.

    The language examples are documented in the iPSC Program Development Guide, 
    chapters 3 and 4 and the VX example is documented in the iPSC VX User's
    Guide. 

